main event: A bright moving object was sighted in Dawson City, Canada on November 16, 1961.
interesting points: The object had regularly illuminating lighting in a circular pattern.
The motion and character of the sighting indicate it was likely a meteor observation.
The object was observed visually by Mr. and Mrs. from Dawson City, who were carpenters aged 45-60.
The object traveled in an arc from south to north and disappeared in a northerly direction.
sighted object: bright moving object with regularly illuminating circular lighting pattern
